%N A396981 Array read by ascending antidiagonals: A(n, k) = A(n, k-A002024(k)) + (n+A002024(k)-1) * A(n-1, k) with A(n, 0) = 0^n, A(0, k) = 1.
%H A396981 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A396981/b396981.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..11324</a> (first 150 antidiagonals, flattened).
%F A396981 A(n, binomial(k,2)) = |Stirling1(n+k, k)|.
%F A396981 Conjecture 1: similarly to |Stirling1(n+k+1, k+1)| = Sum_{j=0..n} |Stirling1(k+j, k)| * (n + k)! / (k + j)! we have A(n, k+f(k)+1) = Sum_{j=0..n} A(j, k) * (n + f(k))! / (f(k) + j)! where f(n) = A002024(n).
%F A396981 Conjecture 2: A(n, k) = Sum_{j=1..k} A(n-1, j + f(j)) for n > 0.
%F A396981 Conjecture 3: Sum_{j=k..n} A(n-j, k + A000217(j)) = |Stirling1(n+1, k+1)|.
%F A396981 Conjecture 4: Sum_{j=0..n} A(n-j, k + A000217(k+m+j)) = A(n, A000217(k+m+1) - m) for n >= 0, k >= 0, m >= 0.
%F A396981 From _Peter Luschny_, Jun 14 2026: (Start)
%F A396981 Let H(n, k) denote the generalized harmonic numbers and C_k = n -> A(n-1, k) for k >= 1.
%F A396981 C_1(n) = (n-1)!.
%F A396981 C_2(n) = n!.
%F A396981 C_3(n) = n!*H(n, 1).
%F A396981 C_4(n) = n!*n.
%F A396981 C_5(n) = n!*((n + 1)*H(n, 1) - n).
%F A396981 C_6(n) = (n+1)!*(H(n+1, 1)^2 - H(n+1, 2))/2.
%F A396981 C_7(n) = (n+1)!*(n + 1 - H(n+1, 1)).
%F A396981 C_8(n) = (n+1)!*((n + 2)*H(n+2, 1) - 2*n - 3).
%F A396981 C_9(n) = (1/2)*(n + 2)!*(H(n+2, 1)^2 - H(n+2, 2) - 2*H(n+2, 1) + 2).
%F A396981 C_10(n) = (1/6)*(n + 2)!*(H(n+2, 1)^3 - 3*H(n+2, 1)*H(n+2, 2) + 2*H(n+2, 3)).
%F A396981 C_11(n) = (n+2)!*(n + 2 - H(n+2, 1) - (H(n+2, 1)^2 - H(n+2, 2))/2).
%F A396981 C_12(n) = (n+2)!*((n + 4)*H(n+2, 1) - 3*n - 6).  (End)
